// Given n non-negative integers representing heights of bars
// in a histogram (each bar has width 1), find the area of
// the largest rectangle that fits entirely within the histogram.
// Constraints: n <= 1e5, h[i] in [0, 1e4]
// Example: h = [2, 1, 5, 6, 2, 3] → 10  (bars h[2]=5, h[3]=6 with width 2)

